Worker dies in buffing machine.
AURANGABAD: A 27-year-old worker died after he got stuck in a buffing machine at Metalman Auto Private Ltd Company in the Waluj industrial area on Saturday, triggering angry protests by workers.
Gokul Raghunath Rathod hailed from Waki village in Kannad taluka of Aurangabad district and was residing at Wadgaon Kolhati in Waluj. He is survived by wife and a year-old son.
The company, which manufactures spare parts for leading automobile firms, closed the operations for the day following the accident and subsequent protests against lake of safety gears. tnn
